.TH NOTEPADX 1 "April 2026" "notepadx 1.3.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
notepadx \- fast native text editor with GPU rendering
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B notepadx
.RI [ file .\|.\|.]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B NotepadX
is a Rust-built text editor focused on making everyday editing feel
immediate, even on large files, without shipping a browser runtime.
.PP
It uses wgpu for GPU-accelerated rendering, ropey for scalable text
storage, and tree-sitter for syntax highlighting across 20 programming
languages.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I file
Open the specified file(s) in tabs on launch. If no files are given,
NotepadX starts with the previous session restored or an empty buffer.
.SH KEYBOARD SHORTCUTS
All shortcuts use Ctrl on Linux (Cmd on macOS).
.TP
.B Ctrl+N
New tab
.TP
.B Ctrl+O
Open file
.TP
.B Ctrl+S
Save
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+S
Save as
.TP
.B Ctrl+W
Close tab
.TP
.B Ctrl+Z
Undo
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+Z
Redo
.TP
.B Ctrl+F
Find
.TP
.B Ctrl+Alt+F
Find & Replace
.TP
.B Ctrl+G
Go to line
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+P
Command palette
.TP
.B Ctrl+,
Settings
.TP
.B Ctrl+D
Select next occurrence
.TP
.B Ctrl+/
Toggle comment
.TP
.B F1
Show keyboard shortcuts
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/notepadx/config.json
User settings (theme, font size, tab size, etc.)
.TP
.I ~/.config/notepadx/session.json
Session state (open tabs, cursor positions, scroll offsets)
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.B NotepadX
requires a GPU-capable display server (X11 or Wayland) with Vulkan
or OpenGL support.
.SH BUGS
Report bugs at https://github.com/szabadkai/NotepadX/issues
